Jane Dulo https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jane_Dulo 0 Jane Dulo (October 13, 1917 – May 22, 1994) was an American actress and comedian. Born Bernice Dewlow, the elder daughter of Lawrence (1890-1947) and Nettie Dewlow (1897-1991), she began her career at the age of ten performing in vaudeville. Her father was a Latvian Jew and her mother was of Lithuanian Jewish descent. She appeared in the television series Hey, Jeannie!, The Phil Silvers Show, The Joey Bishop Show, The Jack Benny Program, McHale's Navy, The Dick Van Dyke Show, Get Smart, Medical Center, The Odd Couple and Gimme a Break!, and others.
